						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar set up before the Sakalēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kōṭa: Gaṇapatidēva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1178, Uttarāyaṇa Saṅkrānti. Mentions a certain Varakavi Guṇḍa at the beginning.</p>						

						<p>Records the remission of the income-tax <hi rend="italic">(āyasuṅka)</hi> due from servants of the temple at Māmaṁḍala by the king, for the merit of his parents.</p>						

						</summary>
